column1: # Use this sheet to define settings for UplinkSet to be created in OneView.
# If the row starts with '#' it will be ignored by the script

column3:
# Accepted values are:
#         Ethernet (Default)
#         FibreChannel
#         FCOE
#         Tunnel
#         Untagged
#         ImageStreamer (N/A for C7000)
# 
# Note: When assigning an Ethernet Network to an ImageStreamer Uplink Set, the network resource must be a Tagged Ethernet Network.
column4:
# Syntax is:
# FlexFabric ----> BAY1:X5|BAY2:X5
#
# VC Fibre Channel ---> BAY3:1|BAY3:2
#
# Synergy VC ---> Enclosure1:Bay3:Q1|Enclosure1:Bay3:Q2|Enclosure2:Bay6:Q1|Enclosure2:Bay6:Q2
#
# Synergy VC Sub-Interface ----> Enclosure1:Bay3:Q1.1|Enclosure1:Bay3:Q2.1|Enclosure2:Bay6:Q1.2|Enclosure2:Bay6:Q2.2
#
# Use | as separator
column6: # Valid name of the Native Ethernet Network
column7:
# Sets the LACP mode on the uplink ports
# Valid for ETHERNET Uplinks only
# Accepted Values:
# Auto (Default)
# Failover
column8:
# Set the LACP Timer value, which sets the lacpdu frequecy to the LACP peer
# Accepted Values:
# Short (Default)
# Long
column9:
# Specify the Primary Uplink Port when EthernetMode is set to FAILOVER.
# Parameter is not valid when EthMode parameter is set to Auto
column10:
# Specify the Fibre Channel Uplink Speed
# Accepted values are:
# Auto
# 2
# 4
# 8
